<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  tal:define="siteName python:view.siteInfo.get_name()">
  <tal:block metal:use-macro="context/@@groupserver_site_home_layout/page">
    <head>
      <title metal:fill-slot="title">
        Page Not Found (404):
        <span tal:replace="siteName"/>
      </title>
      
      <tal:block metal:fill-slot="metadata">
        <meta name="author" content="OnlineGroups.Net" />
        <meta name="description" content="Page not found page" />
      </tal:block>
      
    </head>
    <body>
      <div metal:fill-slot="externallinks" />
      <div metal:fill-slot="sitenavigation" id="sitenavigation">
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a href="/">Home</a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div metal:fill-slot="contextnavigation" />
      <div metal:fill-slot="breadcrumb" />
      <div metal:fill-slot="footer"/>
      
      <div metal:fill-slot="body">
        <h1>Page Not Found</h1>

        <p>Sorry, the page you were trying to get to 
          (<code class="url" tal:content="view/request/URL"/>)
          could not be found.</p>
        <ul tal:condition="view/userRequest" id="user">
          <li>If you <strong>typed</strong> the address, or followed a
            <strong>bookmark</strong>, check the address 
            to ensure the are no mistakes in it.</li>
          <li>If you clicked on a link in an <strong>email</strong> check
            that the link is not split over multiple lines.</li>
        </ul><!--user-->
        <p tal:condition="view/searchRequest" id="search">
          The search results that you used contained links to pages that
          do not exist.
          Hopefully this problem will be automatically fixed over time.  
        </p><!--search-->
        <p tal:condition="view/externalRequest" id="external">
          The link you followed went to this site, but the specific page
          could not be found.
          The administrator of 
          <a tal:attributes="href view/request/HTTP_REFERER" href="#">the
            page you were on</a>
          may be able to correct the link.  
        </p><!--external-->
        <p tal:condition="view/internalRequest" id="internal"
          tal:define="siteId view/siteInfo/id;
            gse python:modules['Products.XWFCore.XWFUtils'].get_support_email;
            supportEmail python:gse(context,siteId);
            m string:The link I followed from ${view/request/HTTP_REFERER} to ${view/request/URL} was broken and I saw a Page Not Found error!;
            msg python:m.replace(' ', '%20')">
          We made a mistake when we created the link that you followed.
          The system has automatically made a note of our error, but if 
          you 
          <a href="#" 
            tal:attributes="href string:mailto:${supportEmail}?Subject=Broken%20Link&body=${msg}"
            class="email">contact us</a> 
          we will get back to you when the link is fixed.
        </p>
        <p>If you want to get all technical about it, 
          <code>404 Not Found</code>. 
          Make of that what you will. 
        </p>
      </div>
    </body>
  </tal:block>
</html>
